        <mxCell id="p1b" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#333D4D;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Has to be structural, enforced at the payment authorization layer itself: spend caps, merchant category limits, per-transaction thresholds. Not a system-prompt instruction the agent&#39;s own reasoning is trusted to honor.  The distinction is the same as a deny-by-default network firewall rule versus a comment in a code review asking a developer to please not open that port." vertex="1">
