        <mxCell id="p2b" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#333D4D;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Has to survive the full transaction chain: protocol layer, payment network authentication, merchant processor. Every party must be able to reconstruct who authorized what, at what spend limit, under what standing instruction, after the fact.  This is structurally the same delegation-chain integrity problem that agent-to-agent coordination protocols have solved for non-commerce cases, applied here to money rather than data." vertex="1">
