        <mxCell id="p3b" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#333D4D;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Has to be explicit before the first disputed transaction. Whose loss is it when an agent purchases wrongly: the platform that built the agent, the payment network, the merchant, or the consumer who set up the standing authorization.  No consistent industry-wide answer exists today. Waiting until the dispute happens to have this conversation for the first time reliably produces a worse outcome." vertex="1">
